{
    "content": "<p>Leaving Dhaka before sunrise, the journey to Sajek feels like stepping out of noise and into silence. The long road through highways, small towns, and finally the hilly terrain of Khagrachari slowly changes the mood of the trip. As the flat concrete views fade away, green hills, winding roads, and fresh air begin to take over. The last stretch from Dighinala to Sajek, with its narrow uphill road and deep valleys on both sides, is both thrilling and unforgettable.</p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p>Reaching Sajek Valley feels like arriving in another world. Clouds float below the hills, cool winds blow across the wooden cottages, and the horizon looks endless. Watching the sunrise from Konglak Hill or simply sitting on a balcony with a cup of tea becomes the highlight of the trip. Sajek is not just a destination—it’s a peaceful escape from the busy rhythm of Dhaka, where time slows down and nature takes the lead.</p>",
    "contentIds": [
        "698c26ce03763778584aed28"
    ]
}

